reviews.text: A bit crowded but the green tea ice cream is really yummy! The taste is so rich, the mochi is very chewy! A very nice dessert place for Japanese dessert!

The best green tea ice cream I have ever tried. It's very creamy with strong yet not too bitter green tea taste. I have been there for over 30 times and never disappointed by their quality. They have a variety of japanese dessert combination. But it's usually crowded and I would recommend getting a take away ice cream then.
Had hojicha and matcha soft serve ice cream. Tasted great!
Flavourful, smooth Japanese ice cream. Menu dishes only, no alterations. Very hyped for some reason. It’s good, but not thaaaat good :p
Delicious ice-cream, very healthy, delicate but intense taste. very refreshing. I loved it.
